"title": "5784: amazement",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "5784",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>Astonishment and surprise are frequent responses to the actions and words of God and Jesus Christ.</p>\n<h2>Amazement at God's actions</h2>\n<h3>His marvellous deeds</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps98:1\">PSA 98:1</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Josh3:5\">JOS 3:5</a> <em>The LORD promises to do amazing things when his people cross the Jordan</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg13:19\">JDG 13:19</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr16:24\">1CH 16:24</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps71:17\">PSA 71:17</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps72:18\">PSA 72:18</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps86:10\">PSA 86:10</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps96:3\">PSA 96:3</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps118:23\">PSA 118:23</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa25:1\">ISA 25:1</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Dan3:24\">DAN 3:24</a> <em>Nebuchadnezzar is amazed at seeing four men in the furnace</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev15:1\">REV 15:1</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev15:3\">REV 15:3</a></p>\n<h3>His creation</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job37:5\">JOB 37:5</a></p>\n<h3>His judgment</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa29:9\">ISA 29:9</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Hab1:5\">HAB 1:5</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John5:28\">JHN 5:28</a></p>\n<h2>Throughout his life Jesus Christ inspired amazement</h2>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt27:14\">MAT 27:14</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark15:5\">MRK 15:5</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke2:33\">LUK 2:33</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke2:47\">LUK 2:47</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke4:22\">LUK 4:22</a></p>\n<h2>Amazement at Jesus Christ's teaching</h2>\n<h3>At his inherent authority</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt7:28-Matt7:29\">MAT 7:28–7:29</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt13:54\">MAT 13:54</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark6:2\">MRK 6:2</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark1:22\">MRK 1:22</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke4:32\">LUK 4:32</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark1:27\">MRK 1:27</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke4:36\">LUK 4:36</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John7:15\">JHN 7:15</a></p>\n<h3>In debate with the Pharisees</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt22:22\">MAT 22:22</a> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark12:17\">MRK 12:17</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke20:26\">LUK 20:26</a></p>\n<h3>In theological debate with the Sadducees</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt22:33\">MAT 22:33</a></p>\n<h3>After talking with the rich young man</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt19:25\">MAT 19:25</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark10:26\">MRK 10:26</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark10:24\">MRK 10:24</a></p>\n<h3>After the cleansing of the temple</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark11:18\">MRK 11:18</a></strong> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke19:47\">LUK 19:47</a> <em>Here the crowds' amazement causes the chief priests and teachers of the law to fear Jesus Christ.</em></p>\n<h2>Amazement at Jesus Christ's revelation of himself</h2>\n<p><em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke24:41\">LUK 24:41</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John5:20\">JHN 5:20</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Thess1:10\">2TH 1:10</a></p>\n<h2>Amazement at Jesus Christ's miracles</h2>\n<h3>Miracles of healing</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt15:31\">MAT 15:31</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt9:8\">MAT 9:8</a> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark2:12\">MRK 2:12</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke5:26\">LUK 5:26</a> <em>at the healing of the paralytic</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark5:42\">MRK 5:42</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke8:56\">LUK 8:56</a> <em>at the healing of Jairus' daughter</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts3:10-Acts3:11\">ACT 3:10–3:11</a> <em>at the healing of the crippled beggar</em></p>\n<h3>The casting out of demons</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark1:27\">MRK 1:27</a></strong> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt9:33\">MAT 9:33</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke11:14\">LUK 11:14</a>; \n<a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark5:20\">MRK 5:20</a> <em>Legion</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke9:43\">LUK 9:43</a> <em>a boy with an evil spirit</em></p>\n<h3>Miracles of nature</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt8:27\">MAT 8:27</a></strong> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke8:25\">LUK 8:25</a> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt21:20\">MAT 21:20</a> <em>the withered fig-tree</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark6:51\">MRK 6:51</a> <em>Jesus Christ walking on the water</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke5:9\">LUK 5:9</a> <em>the miraculous haul of fish</em></p>\n<h2>Amazement at the coming of the Holy Spirit and subsequent events</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts2:12\">ACT 2:12</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts2:7\">ACT 2:7</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts8:13\">ACT 8:13</a> <em>Simon's amazement at the miracles performed by Philip</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts9:21\">ACT 9:21</a> <em>amazement at the change in Saul</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts10:45\">ACT 10:45</a> <em>astonishment at the Holy Spirit being poured out on the Gentiles</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts12:16\">ACT 12:16</a> <em>amazement at Peter's release from prison</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts13:12\">ACT 13:12</a></p>\n<h2>Jesus Christ himself experienced amazement</h2>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark6:6\">MRK 6:6</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke7:9\">LUK 7:9</a></p>",
